content:
@jmo, can you elaborate on your vote on Monkey? It looks like it was simply because he gave Hoopla a town read (judging from your questions at #132). Do you have any town reads yourself? I don't like how jmo seems to be floating under the radar. You didn't even address #88 by KBW.<br>
<br>
<br>
@blue yoshi, what do you think about #73 by Chenoan? By the way, mario has language difficulties in case you haven't noticed.<br>
<br>
<br>
@Chevre, would you be happy with lynching Chenoan? Or is your vote for pressure? Town reads?<br>
<br>
<br>
@Doc, if you think enomis is scum, why are you not pursuing your case or even asking questions from enomis? It looks to me like you casted your vote on enomis and left it there just to have your vote somewhere. Why do you think Monkey prematurely assuming Hoopla as town is "fine"? Are you saying that early town assumptions is pro-town? By the way, you ignored #96 by KBW. What do you think about #73?

@Hoopla: I typically point out my pressure votes if that's indeed what they are for. It helps distinguish an information request from a campaign to lynch. I've used this in <a href="http://forums.mtgsalvation.com/showpost.php?p=10004358&amp;postcount=168" class="postlink">other games</a> as town. I've had the whole argument of whether it's still a pressure vote if the target knows that it's a pressure vote (I think in that linked game but I couldn't locate it, probably in the Xyre exchange). I concluded that both ways have benefits depending on what you want your vote to do.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I think this is a good lynch. MonkeyMan has been decidedly anti-town and showed no interest in reversing that opinion.

@Chevre, expanding on my scumtell of talking to every player, I want to add that it feels like you are trying to hide any connection with scumbuddies. This stops people from finding links between you and certain players. I don't feel that a townie would address everyone rather than just their scumreads, it is also scummy because you do this in almost every single post, if you were actually scumhunting I think you would eventually slim down to a smaller pool of players to concentrate on. I'm not sure if this is just your playstyle but addressing multiple players is a rare practice and just seems to me like trying really hard to obscure your links with players.<br>
<br>
I don't feel a genuine town mindset with questions such as in #141 where you asked me whether I would be happy with an enomis lynch, when I wasn't even voting enomis. It was so random and just feels like you are trying to look busy or create fake content. It's like if I suddenly asked Hoopla if she would be happy with an Elyse lynch when Hoopla isn't even voting Elyse. I also didn't like how you asked me "how did you realise mario's vote was not on you". I explained it several times throughout the thread and even if you missed it, you could easily read mario's post and figure it out after he said he wasn't voting for me.

@Nul: I thought you were fairly sure Jmo was scum? Why the unvote when the roleclaim doesn't swing Jmo either way on the alignment.<br>
<br>
No wonder hoopla is hoopla.

@Chevre: It was the hoopla post.<br>
<br>
@ac: Mind answering my question?

@Majiffy, it helps if you give reasons for your scum reads so people can decide whether or not to join your wagon.<br>
<br>
@Jmo, so your scumreads are AC and Majiffy? You really think Majiffy would replace in and push a lynch on his scumbuddy?<br>
<br>
@Chevre, what do you think about Hoopla's case on you? Would you be happy with a Jmo lynch seeing as you are still on the wagon?<br>
<br>
I have a feeling Elyse is town and Majiffy is also slightly leaning town despite Chenoan's earlier play.

@ac<br>
That's really bad reasoning, and it looks like you are just trying to eek out mislynches and hope to ride it to the end of the game.<br>
<br>
@jmo<br>
How do you know there are three scum?

Elyse, hoopla is town, there is no way jmo decided to claim that he rolestopped two of his buddy.<br>
<br>
@hoopla: dont you think a miller make the alr weak town weaker? Especially when scum team is quite strong.

If you can't get a read on people does that mean you are just stabbing in the dark?  You should use facts to back up your votes or at least make some up to look like you are trying.  People have different play styles that you have to get used too.  I don't know everyone on the site but I still do my best to get reads on people.  As of right now you are just making excuses and have still ignored the questions that I gave you.  You are just solidifying yourself as my scum read.<br>
<br>
@everyone else: Why are you not posting?  I guarantee there is something you can at least comment on by this point of me joining.  Also, if I am not mistaken the deadline is about to be unfrozen so unless we want to no lynch the today and the next day then we need to decide on a lynch target.  We can't get anywhere if none of you are posting.
